This paper deals with energy-efficient information transfer and communication protocols in RF-powered networks, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization techniques for maximizing throughput, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel RF energy harvesting architecture, which involves the integration of hardware and system design, making it relevant to the subfield of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also involves numerical simulations and performance evaluation, which are typically studied in multimedia (cs.MM) and computer engineering (cs.CE) subfields.
